Interpretation Act 1889 in its application to this section, the 1889 c. 63.
proper address of a person, in the case of a secretary or clerk of
abody corporate, shall be that of the registered or principal office
of that body, in the case of a partner of a firm shall be that
of the principal office of the firm, and in any other case shall be
the last known address of the person to be served .
