extinguish that liability if a complaint by the employee
were not time-barred as described in that subsection.
(4) The Secretary of State shall make provision by regulations
as to the making of claims for rebates under this section and
such regulations may in particular-
( a) require a claim to be made within such time limit as
may be prescribed ; and
( b) require a claim to be supported by such evidence as
may be prescribed.
