(b) the Redundancy Payments Act 1965 ;
1965 с. 62.
as if she had been employed until the notified day of return,
and, if she would not otherwise be so treated, as having been
continuously employed until that day, and as if she had been
dismissed with effect from that day for the reason for which
she was not permitted to return .
( 2) The provisions of Schedule 3 to this Act shall have effect
for the purpose of supplementing the foregoing provisions of
this Act relating to an employee's right to return to work.
