( 3) A notice given under this section may be varied or revoked
by a subsequent notice so given.
( 4 ) If a person refuses or wilfully neglects to furnish any
information which he has been required to furnish by a notice
under subsection (1) above, he shall be liable on summary
conviction to a fine not exceeding £ 100.
( 5 ) If a person , in purporting to comply with a requirement of
a notice under subsection ( 1) above, knowingly or recklessly
makes any false statement he shall be liable on summary
conviction to a fine not exceeding £ 400.
