taken of employees whom he proposes to dismiss as redundant
in respect of whose proposed dismissals notice has already been
given to the Secretary of State.
c.71
2188 Employment Protection Act 1975
PART IV
( 3) A notice under this section shall-
( a ) be given to the Secretary of State by delivery to him
or by sending it by post to him, at such address as
the Secretary of State may direct in relation to the
establishment where the employees proposed to be
dismissed are employed ;
