the Lord Chancellor or, as the case may be, the Secretary of State
to be necessary or expedient in consequence of their partial
operation ( whether before, on or after the day appointed by the
order ).
(6) Sections 127 and 128 above and any provision of this Act
which amends or repeals any provision of the House of Commons 1975 c. 24.
Disqualification Act 1975 or the Northern Ireland Assembly 1975 c. 25.
Disqualification Act 1975 shall extend to Northern Ireland, but
except as aforesaid this Act shall not extend there.
