(c) the person applying for custody is a person qualified,
in terms of subsections (3) to (8) of section 33 of this
Act, to apply in England or Wales for a custodianship
order in respect of the child.
( 2) For the purposes of this section, " the court " means-
(a ) the Court of Session ; or
(b) the sheriff court of the sheriffdom within which the child
resides.
