8B of this licence ;
(b) deliveries of petroleum in accordance with clause 8C
of this licence ; and
(c) payments in accordance with Schedule 2 to this licence.
2. After clause 8 of the relevant clauses there shall be inserted
the following clauses : -
Royalty
payments. 8A.- (1) Subject to paragraphs ( 2 ) to ( 4) of this
clause the Licensee shall pay to the Minister , in respect
of each half year in which this licence is in force ( here-
after in this clause and in clause 8B of this licence
Petroleum and Submarine Pipe-lines Act 1975 c. 74 2487
referred to as a " chargeable period "), a royalty of an
amount equal to 124 per cent. of the value of the
petroleum relating to that period.
( 2 ) The Licensee shall not be required to make a
payment in pursuance ursuance of paragraph (1) of this clause in
respect of a chargeable period if he is required by virtue
of clause 8C of this licence to deliver to the Minister
all the royalty petroleum for that period.
( 3) The Licensee shall not be required to make a pay-
ment in pursuance of paragraph (1) of this clause in
respect of a chargeable period if he is required by virtue
of clause 8C of this licence to deliver to the Minister
some but not all of the royalty petroleum for that period ;
but in respect of that period the Licensee shall, subject
to paragraph ( 4 ) of this clause, pay to the Minister a
royalty of an amount determined in accordance with the
formula-
A( 12 -B)
100-B
where A is the value of the petroleum relating to that
period and B is the number of per cent. in the percentage
which the royalty petroleum required to be delivered to
the Minister in that period is of the petroleum won and
