PART VI 56.-(1 ) Where an offence under this Act which has been
Offences by committed by a body corporate is proved to have been com-
Corporations. mitted with the consent or connivance of , or to be attributable
to any neglect on the part of, a director, manager, secretary or
other similar officer of the body corporate, or any person who
was purporting to act in any such capacity, he, as well as the
body corporate, shall be guilty of that offence and liable to be
proceeded against accordingly.
( 2) Where the affairs of a body corporate are managed by
its members, this section shall apply in relation to acts and
defaults of a member in connection with his functions of
management as if he were a director of the body corporate.
