planning authority or the district planning authority, as the case may
require .
( 6 ) An order under this paragraph shall not be made unless a
draft of the order has been approved by a resolution of each House
of Parliament.
4.- (1 ) Where a compulsory purchase order authorising the
acquisition of any land is submitted to the Secretary of State in
accordance with Part I of Schedule 1 then, if the Secretary of
State-
( a ) is satisfied that the order ought to be confirmed so far
