15.-( 1 ) Without prejudice to his general duties under any Health
Act of Parliament or otherwise, it shall be the duty of the control.
Secretary of State and, to such extent as he may direct, of the
Authority, to make such arrangements as appear to him to be
necessary—
( a) for preventing danger to public health from aircraft
arriving at any aerodrome owned or managed by the
Authority ; and
( b) for preventing the spread of infection by means of any
aircraft leaving any such aerodrome, so far as may be
necessary or expedient for the purpose of carrying out
any treaty, convention, arrangement or engagement
with any country.
( 2) A local authority may, and shall if the Secretary of State
so requires, undertake duties in connection with the execution
of any such arrangements as aforesaid, and the Secretary of State
shall pay to the local authority such charges as the local
