Statutory Corporations ( Financial Provisions) Act 1974
( 1974 с. 8)
1975
= Statutory Corporations (Financial Provisions) Act 1975
(1975 с. 55 )
By the Transfer of Functions (Civil Aviation ) Order 1966 (S.I.
1966/741) the functions of the Minister of Aviation with respect to
civil aviation were, with certain exceptions ( which did not include
his functions under any of the enactments proposed to be repealed ) ,
transferred to the Board of Trade.
By the Secretary of State for Trade and Industry Order 1970
(S.I. 1970/1537 ) all functions of the Board of Trade were trans-
ferred, so as to be exercisable concurrently with the Board, to the
Secretary of State.
By the Secretary of State for Employment and Productivity
Order 1968 (S.I. 1968/729) all functions of the Minister of Labour
were transferred to the Secretary of State.
The effect of these instruments has not been acknowledged
against each of the enactments affected.
