1858 = The Election of Members during Recess Act 1858
( 21 & 22 Vict. c. 110. )
1863 The Election in the Recess Act 1863
( 26 & 27 Vict. c. 20. )
1872 = The Bankruptcy (Ireland) Amendment Act 1872
( 35 & 36 Vict. c. 58.)
1883 = The Bankruptcy Act 1883
( 46&47 Vict. c. 52. )
1913 = The Bankruptcy (Scotland) Act 1913
( 3 & 4Geo. 5. с. 20.)
1. Section 5 of the Act of 1858 applied the general provisions of the Act of 1784.
2. The provisions reproduced in s. 4 of the Act were applied to bankruptcy
cases, in Ireland by section 44 of the 1872 Act and in England and Wales by section
33(3) of the 1883 Act. They also extended to Scottish bankruptcy cases because
of the application of the latter subsection to Scotland by section 184 of the 1913 Act.
